            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-9 col-md-9 text-center" role="main">
                    
    <h2 class="h2" id="independent">Asking For Help With Independent Work</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <li class="item">Each of you lovely students will have a trifold that says on one side "Need me some help!" and
                        on the other it will say "Keep working." So when you need help you will face the "Need me some help!
                        side towards me, so that the "Keep Working" side is facing towards you. This is so that while you
                        wait for help, you are reminded to move on and keep working while you wait. No need to stop and
                        get a lesser grade when you can get a higher one if you continue on.</li>
        <img src="/static/img/help_sign.png" />
        <img src="/static/img/help_sign_keep_working.png" />
    </div>

    <h2 class="h2" id="centers">Asking For Help When at Centers</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <li class="item">Before you ask me, see if anybody else knows the answer.</li>
        <li class="item">If no one knows the answer then the entire group will face the "Need me some help!" side of the
                        trifold towards me so that way I know they need help.</li>
    </div>

    <h2 class="h2" id="cooperative">Asking For Help When Doing Cooperative Learning</h2>
    <hr class="subtitle"/>
    <div class="list-group">
        <li class="item">Same as centers, before you ask, try asking one of your partners. They may know the answer.</li>
        <li class="item">It no one knows the answer everyone can turn their trifold saying "Need me some help" is facing
                        the center of the group.</li>
    </div>

                </div>
